Name: Aban
Meaning: Fortress (or castle). Strength, seat of power, authority, and magnificence.

Name: Abe Dua
Meaning: Palm tree. A symbol of wealth, resourcefulness, and self-sufficiency.

Name: Adinkrahene
Meaning: King of the Adinkra symbols. A symbol for authority, leadership, and charisma, qualities associated with kings.

Name: Adwo
Meaning: Calmness. A symbol for peace, tranquility, and quiet.

Name: Agyin Dawuru
Meaning: Agyin's gong. A symbol of faithfulness, alertness, and dutifulness.

Name: Akoben
Meaning: War horn. A symbol of a call to action, readiness to be called to action, readiness, and voluntarism.

Name: Akofena
Meaning: A sword of war (or the state ceremonial swords). A symbol of state authority, legality, the legitimized authority of a ruler, recognition of gallantry of heroic deeds.

Name: Akoko Nan
Meaning: The foot of a hen. A symbol for discipline coupled with care and nurturing.

Name: Akoma
Meaning: Heart. A symbol of love, goodwill, patience, faithfulness, fondness, endurance, and consistency.

Name: Akoma Ntoaso
Meaning: Joining of hearts. A symbol of agreement, togetherness and unity or a charter. An amplification of the concept of Akoma

Name: Ananse Ntentan (Ananse Ntontan)
Meaning: Spider's web. A symbol of wisdom, craftiness, creativity, and the complexities of life.

Name: Ani Bere A Enso Gya
Meaning: A symbol of patience, self-containment, self-discipline, and self-control.

Name: Asase Ye Duru
Meaning: The earth has weight. A symbol of providence and the divinity of Mother Earth.

Name: Aya
Meaning: Fern. A symbol of endurance, independence, defiance against difficulties, hardiness, perseverance, and resourcefulness.

Name: Bese Saka
Meaning: Bunch of cola nuts. A symbol of affluence, power, abundance, and plenty. Also a symbol of togetherness and unity

Name: Bi Nka Bi
Meaning: Fern. A symbol of endurance, independence, defiance against difficulties, hardiness, perseverance, and resourcefulness.

Name: Dame Dame
Meaning: Checkered. A symbol of craftiness, intelligence, and strategy.

Name: Denkyem
Meaning: Crocodile. A symbol of adaptability and cleverness.

Name: Dono
Meaning: The tension talking drum. A symbol of appelation, praise, goodwill and rhythm.

Name: Dono Ntoaso
Meaning: The double dono; joined tension talking drum. A symbol of united action, alertness, goodwill, praise, rejoicing, and adroitness.

Name: Duafe
Meaning: Wooden comb. A symbol of feminine consideration or good feminine qualities such as patience, prudence, fondness, love, and care.

Name: Dwennimmen
Meaning: Ram's horns. A symbol of strength (in mind, body, and soul), humility, wisdom, and learning.

Name: Eban
Meaning: Fence. A symbol of safety, security, and love.

Name: Epa
Meaning: Handcuffs. A symbol of law and justice.

Name: Ese ne Tekrema
Meaning: Teeth and tongue. A symbol of improvement, advancement, growth, the need for friendliness and interdependence.

Name: Fafanto
Meaning: Butterfly. A symbol of tenderness, gentleness, honesty, and fragility.

Name: Fihankra
Meaning: An enclosed or secured compound house. A symbol of brotherhood, safety, security, completeness, and solicarity.

Name: Fofo
Meaning: A flowering plant (bidens pilosa). A symbol of warning against jealousy and covetousness.

Name: Funtumfunefu Denkyemfunefu
Meaning: Conjoined crocodiles. A symbol of unity in diversity giving a common destiny; sharing.

Name: Gyawu Atiko
Meaning: The back of Gyawu's head. A symbol of valor and bravery.

Name: Gye Nyame
Meaning: Except God. A symbol expressing the omnipotence of God.

Name: Hwehwemudua
Meaning: Measuring rod (rod of investigation) or rule. A symbol of excellence, superior quality, perfection, knowledge, and critical examination.

Name: Hye Wo Nhye
Meaning: Burn you won't burn (fig. unburnable). A symbol of toughness, imperishability, and permanence.

Name: Kramo Bone Amma Yeanhu Kramo Pa
Meaning: A symbol of warning against deception and hypocrisy.

Name: Kuronti ne Akwamu
Meaning: Kuronti and Akwamu. A symbol of democracy, sharing ideas, taking council.

Name: Kwatakye Atiko
Meaning: The back of Kwatakye's head. A symbol of valor and bravery.

Name: Mako
Meaning: Peppers. A symbol of inequality and uneven development.

Name: Menso Wo Kenten
Meaning: A symbol of industry, self-reliance, and economic self-determination.

Name: Mframadan
Meaning: Well-ventilated house. A symbol of resilience and readiness to face the vicissitudes of life.

Name: Mmere Dane
Meaning: Time chanegs (times change). A symbol of the temporariness of good times.

Name: Mpatapo
Meaning: Pacification knot. A symbol of pacification, forgiveness, and reconciliation.

Name: Mpuannum
Meaning: Five tufts (of hair). A symbol of loyalty and priestly office

Name: Nea Onnim
Meaning: He who does not know can still get to know.

Name: Nkonsonkonson
Meaning: Chain. A symbol of unity, community.

Name: Nkyinkyim
Meaning: Twisting. A symbol representing the tortuous nature of life's journey.

Name: Nsaa
Meaning: A type of woven cloth, renowned for its quality. A symbol of excellence, genuineness, and authenticity.

Name: Nsoromma
Meaning: Star (literally, "child of the heavens"). Faith and the belief in patronage and dependency on a supreme being

Name: Nteasee
Meaning: Understanding. A symbol for understanding and cooperation.

Name: Nyame Biribi Wo Soro
Meaning: God, there is something in the heavens. From the saying. A symbol of hope and inspiration."God, there is something up there (in the heavens); let it come to me."

Name: Nyame Dua
Meaning: God's tree (sacred stump). A symbol of God's presence and protection.

Name: Nyame Nwu Na Mawu
Meaning: A symbol expressing the immortality of the human soul.

Name: Odo Nnyew Fie Kwan
Meaning: Love does not lose its way home. Those led by love always end up in the right place.

Name: Okuafo Pa
Meaning: Good farmer. A symbol of diligence, hard work, and entrepreneurship.

Name: Osram ne Nsoromma
Meaning: Moon and star. A symbol of faithfulness, fondness, harmony, benevolence, love, loyalty, and femininity.

Name: Owuo Atwedee
Meaning: Ladder of death. A symbol of the certainty and universality of death.

Name: Sankofa
Meaning: Go back and get it! A symbol of the wisdom of learning from the past to build for the future.

Name: Sepow
Meaning: Executioner's knife. A symbol of justice.

Name: Tamfo Bebre
Meaning: The enemy will suffer; the enemy will stew in his own juice. A symbol for ill-will, jealousy, and envy.

Name: UAC Nkanea
Meaning: UAC lights. A symbol of technological advancement.

Name: Wawa Aba
Meaning: Seed of the wawa tree. A symbol of hardiness, toughness, and perseverance.

Name: Woforo Dua Pa A
Meaning: When you climb a good tree. A symbol of support for good causes.
